@dsqx71 There are many lines of duplicate codes that should be refactored. Consider the following alternatives:
1. create a base class for conv rnns and use that for shared logic. put the rest specialization in each children.
2. create a container class for conv rnns that accepts other RNN cells as constructor argument, and make it pluggable.

I reopen this issue, because I have a idea ,"How about add ‘layout=NTC’ parameter in mx.contrib.sym.ctc_loss(data,label,layout) , like unroll() in mxnet.rnn.BaseRNNCell()~", and another question,normally, the output of rnn.unroll() has the shape of (seq_len, batch_size, num_hidden)[layout='NTC'], and the 'data' of mx.contrib.sym.ctc_loss(data,label) need the shape
 (seq_len, batch_size, alphabet_size + 1), it means I need to add a FC layer (with num_hidden=alphabet_size+1) before mx.contrib.sym.ctc_loss ?
@sbodenstein

I have figured out something to implement a new iterator, but there is one thing I am confused. I want to make each batch have two types of labels, like DATABATCH((image), (label1, label2)), but I have gone through the code and haven't got a solution. 
In each of the already done iterators in C++, I found there is one variable called _out to hold the current batch of data. The type of this variable is "DataInst". From the definition of this type.
```
struct DataInst {
  /*! \brief unique id for instance */
  unsigned index;
  /*! \brief content of data */
  std::vector<TBlob> data;
  /*! \brief extra data to be fed to the network */
  std::string extra_data;
};  // struct DataInst
```
It seems it only has a vector of TBlob. So how do we distinguish between data and labels if we want multiple types of labels of even data? Thanks. @piiswrong @tqchen @mli
